From: LunaOS Project <lunaos@puredarwin.org>
Date: 2026-02-28
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] agx: Darwin arm64 stub — Apple GPU Vulkan

AGX is the Apple GPU in all Apple Silicon chips (M1/M2/M3/M4).
The Asahi Linux project has an open-source AGX driver (Mesa "agx" gallium
driver + DRM kernel driver). LunaOS can port this to Darwin once the
AGXAccelerator IOKit KEXT is written.

This stub:
  - Compiles the agx Mesa driver for arm64 Darwin
  - Probes for "agx" DRM driver name at VkCreateInstance time
  - Falls back to lavapipe if AGX KEXT is not loaded
  - Logs: "agx: Apple GPU not found via DRM. TODO_agx_kext: port
    Asahi agx driver as Darwin KEXT. Falling back to lavapipe."

Asahi reference: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/asahi/mesa (agx branch)
TODO_agx_kext: Port linux/drivers/gpu/drm/asahi → IOKit KEXT.
  The Asahi team's drm-asahi kernel driver is the reference.
  On Darwin, this needs to talk to AGXAccelerator (Apple's closed GPU fw).
  Alternative: use IOAcceleratorFamily2 like macOS does (requires reverse eng).

MoltenVK alternative: If AGX KEXT porting is too complex, MoltenVK
provides Vulkan 1.2 over Metal on Apple Silicon with good performance.
Enable with: brew install molten-vk
---
diff --git a/src/asahi/vulkan/agx_device.c b/src/asahi/vulkan/agx_device.c
--- a/src/asahi/vulkan/agx_device.c
+++ b/src/asahi/vulkan/agx_device.c
@@ -1,5 +1,42 @@
 #include "agx_private.h"
 
+#ifdef MESA_DARWIN_ARM64
+/*
+ * Darwin arm64 AGX stub.
+ *
+ * AGX is Apple's GPU. On Linux (Asahi), the DRM driver is "asahi".
+ * On Darwin, there is no open DRM driver for AGX yet.
+ *
+ * Probe path: open /dev/dri/renderD128, check DRM_IOCTL_VERSION.
+ *   If driver name == "agx" or "asahi" → AGX KEXT loaded → proceed
+ *   Otherwise → return VK_ERROR_INCOMPATIBLE_DRIVER → lavapipe takes over
+ *
+ * MoltenVK path (alternative, works NOW on real Apple Silicon):
+ *   If libMoltenVK.dylib is found, the Vulkan loader will pick it up
+ *   automatically via its ICD manifest. No changes needed here.
+ *
+ * TODO_agx_kext: Steps to enable hardware AGX Vulkan on Darwin:
+ *   1. Port drm-asahi (https://github.com/AsahiLinux/linux tree,
+ *      drivers/gpu/drm/asahi) as an IOKit KEXT for Darwin/XNU
+ *   2. Or: wrap AGXAccelerator.kext (Apple's closed GPU firmware handler)
+ *      with an open DRM-compatible interface
+ *   3. Rename agx_icd.aarch64.json.disabled → agx_icd.aarch64.json
+ *   4. Mesa agx gallium + Vulkan driver activates automatically
+ */
+#include <fcntl.h>
+#include <sys/ioctl.h>
+#include "drm_darwin.h"
+
+static bool darwin_has_agx(void) {
+    int fd = open("/dev/dri/renderD128", O_RDWR | O_CLOEXEC);
+    if (fd < 0) return false;
+    char name[64] = {};
+    struct drm_version ver = { .name = name, .name_len = sizeof(name)-1 };
+    bool ok = (ioctl(fd, DRM_IOCTL_VERSION, &ver) == 0 &&
+               (strncmp(name, "agx", 3) == 0 ||
+                strncmp(name, "asahi", 5) == 0));
+    close(fd);
+    return ok;
+}
+
+VkResult agx_darwin_check_device(void) {
+    if (!darwin_has_agx()) {
+        mesa_loge("agx: Apple GPU not found via DRM.\n"
+                  "TODO_agx_kext: port Asahi agx driver as Darwin KEXT,\n"
+                  "or install MoltenVK (brew install molten-vk) for Metal-backed Vulkan.\n"
+                  "Falling back to lavapipe (software Vulkan 1.4).");
+        return VK_ERROR_INCOMPATIBLE_DRIVER;
+    }
+    return VK_SUCCESS;
+}
+#endif /* MESA_DARWIN_ARM64 */
